title: Lyon manager injured after team bus attacked before Marseille match
description: The manager of Lyon has been injured after the team bus was attacked on its way to the stadium ahead of a match against Marseille.

title: Russian airport closed after 'anti-Israel protesters' storm runway
description: An airport in Russia was forced to close after 'anti-Israel protesters' stormed the runway.

title: Six dead after two trains collide in India
description: Six people have died and 40 left injured after two trains collided in southern India on Sunday.

title: Completely cut off - it's impossible to know if Gaza will return to any kind of 'normal'
description: I've covered many of the Israeli incursions into Gaza over the years, mainly, it has to be said, from inside the narrow enclave.

title: Inside Gaza hospital where hundreds shelter despite Israeli evacuation orders
description: Hundreds of people including young children and babies line the corridors of a Gaza City hospital, which the Israeli authorities have ordered to evacuate, according to the Palestinian Red Crescent Society (PRCS).

title: Israel will not leave hostages behind but this challenge is on a scale the country has not faced before
description: Israel has warned of a long war to defeat Hamas, but it will surely be hoping to achieve its other main objective much faster - the rescue of more than 200 hostages.

title: Toddlers 'hired' in Japanese nursing home to tackle loneliness
description: The pitter-patter of tiny feet and giggles are sounds frequently heard at one Japanese nursing home.

title: Gazans frantically try to reconnect with loved ones as internet access returns
description: A total communication blackout struck Gaza on Friday night as the territory came under heavy Israeli bombardment.

title: Liverpool striker's parents kidnapped in Colombia
description: The parents of Liverpool striker Luis Diaz were kidnapped in Colombia after being stopped by gunmen on motorbikes.
